The Basque catalog took 198.5 seconds to generate and returned no body from
the previous non-streamed Responses request before its 180-second timeout.
`tools/translate-po` therefore sends at most 20 PO entries per streamed
request, requires `response.completed`, and treats a 60-second byte-idle gap
as failed. GNU gettext accepts compatible printf directives, so
`msgfmt --check-format` alone does not reject `%d` in place of `%'d`, and it
skips entries that extraction did not flag as `c-format`; the helper must
compare every detected printf directive sequence exactly before it atomically
updates a catalog.
